  <description type="morphology">Leaves oblanceolate to lance-linear. Peduncles 30–50 mm. Involucres 5–7 mm. Phyllaries ± 8, distinct, oblanceolate, apices acute. Ray florets 8; corollas yellow, laminae 2–7 mm (w San Joaquin Valley) or 9–17 mm (se San Joaquin Valley), entire or slightly lobed (mid lobes shorter than outers). Disc florets 20–40. Cypselae ± prismatic, not obcompressed, 2.5–3 mm, 3-angled (ray) or 4-angled (disc), uniformly gray-strigose. 2n = 26.</description>
